diagnosis.final_diagnosis: Recanalization of anterior communicating artery aneurysm
diagnosis.diagnostic_reasoning: The final diagnosis was supported by the detection of contrast agent inside and around the WEB device during digital subtraction angiography (DSA), and the need for surgical clipping was discussed during an interdisciplinary neurovascular team conference due to the aneurysm's wide-neck configuration and the associated risks of long-term platelet inhibition.
